pons I still hit normally.  I was not getting an IMMUNE message like when you need a magic weapon.  My gauntlets are magical also.  It appears that mobs can now mitigate damage all the way to a miss, and was wondering if any of you had noticed the same phenominon <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=252504" target="top">Xath Carnage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xathcarnage>Xath Carnage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 8:38:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mitigating to misses now?</span><hr size=1> Hmm ok well i dueled a paladin with 1300 ac and could easily hit him with my fists for above minimum damage.  I hit regularly and got at least 1 hit for 16.  Maybe mobs are different, or it could be a warrior thing, or it could be that 1300 was just not enough ac.  It doesnt seem that the ac requirement was that high, as a rusted model in PoI was mitigating all my hits to misses.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=252504" target="top">Xath Carnage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilerboy>pilerboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 8:48:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mitigating to misses now?</span><hr size=1> Heh I was buck naked after being rezzed in NToV and I hit Lord Vyemm (while he was at 1% health), for 1 10 